          <num>346-12</num>
          <heading>Hearing</heading>
          <content>
            <p>§346-12  Hearing.
An applicant or
recipient, deeming oneself aggrieved, shall be entitled to appeal to the
director in the manner prescribed by department rules and shall be afforded
reasonable notice and opportunity for a hearing at which all of the evidence
presented by the parties, to the extent allowed by chapter 91, shall be
considered in a fair and impartial manner. [L 1941, c 296, §1(8); RL 1945,
§4808; RL 1955, §107-8; HRS §346-12; am L 1970, c 105, §5; gen ch 1985; am L
1987, c 339, §4; am L 2004, c 207, §1]
Cross References
Hearings, see chapter 91.
Case Notes
Section together with 45 CFR 2505.10, satisfies due process. 
66 H. 489, 666 P.2d 1135 (1983).
